The low energy region between 525 eV and 534 eV is the region of main interest in this work and a detailed view is presented in Fig. 3b,c. This low energy region typically originates from electronic transitions from the O1s shell to transition metal 3d orbitals hybridized with oxygen 2p orbitals28,48,53–55. Four peaks could be distinguished at 529 eV, 529.9 eV, 531.2 eV and 532.5 eV. We assign these to the transitions from O(1 s) to O(2p) orbitals mixed with Ni(3d)t2g, Fe(3d)t2g, O(π\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
